train-info

Display information of arriving and departing trains at any Swedish
train station. Can also be used to retrieve  information of a train 
according to it's number. Most of the output is in Swedish.

***** USAGE EXAMPLE *****

train-info "Stockholm C"

STOCKHOLM C
Avgående:
Tid   Till          Ny Tid  Spår  Tåg
14:40 Norrköping C  14:45   12a   237
15:10 Göteborg C            12    439
15:11 Uppsala C             3     840
15:14 Köpenhamn             11    539
15:17 Göteborg C            10  89641
15:23 Gävle C               17    278
15:29 Oslo                  12     55
15:36 Hallsberg             10    139
15:37 Västerås C            6     790
15:40 Kolmården             12a   239
Ankommande:
Tid   Till          Ny Tid  Spår  Tåg
15:16 Linköping C   15:16   17    278
15:30 Gävle C               11    275
15:31 Hallsberg             18b   134
15:40 Karlstad C            17b   634
15:40 Sundsvall C           7     575
15:49 Uppsala C             3     845
15:50 Malmö C               19b   534
15:50 Göteborg C            18b   434
15:53 Örebro C              8     743
16:05 Eskilstuna C          19b   942

Tåginformation från Tåg.Info (http://tåg.info)


Using train-info to retrieve information about a specific train:

train-info 820

================================================================================
Tåg 820 (SJ Regional) Stockholm C (10:11) - Uppsala C (10:51) [2012-01-23]
Status: avgick från Stockholm C kl 10:11
Mer info: http://xn--tg-yia.info/20120123/820
================================================================================

Tåget gör uppehåll i: 

========== [1] Stockholm C ==========
Ordinarie Avgångstid: 10:11
Avgick: 10:11

========== [2] Märsta ==========
Ordinarie Ankomsttid: 10:31
Ordinarie Avgångstid: 10:31
Ankom: 10:30
Avgick: 10:32

========== [3] Knivsta ==========
Ordinarie Ankomsttid: 10:39
Ordinarie Avgångstid: 10:39
Ankom: 10:39
Avgick: 10:41

========== [4] Uppsala C ==========
Ordinarie Ankomsttid: 10:51

Tåginformation från Tåg.Info (http://tåg.info)


***** HOW TO RUN *****
requires: jdk, ant

0) git clone git@github.com:rojters/train-info.git 
1) ant compile
2) ant jar

Run using the train-info script OR java -jar

Try it out with:

> train-info ./"Stockholm C"

If you find it usefull you can put the jar file and script in some folder that's in your PATH.

***** FAQ *****
Q: Hold on, how can I be sure to trust this information? What if I miss my train!
A: The program uses the tåg.info API which in turn uses information available @ Trafikverket
(the Swedish Transport Administration) and is the agency responsible for all railway traffic.
